         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Facilities management for high temperature research centre</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>FRAM341/17</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="79993100"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>VEAT notice of the University of Birmingham's intention to award a contract to Mitie Technical Facilities Management to provide a total facilities management service for its High Temperature Research Centre (HTRC) facility on the Ansty Research Park in Coventry. The HTRC is a University of Birmingham building collaborating with Rolls-Royce to develop the next generation of fan turbine blades.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1047727.20</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKG33"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Ansty Research Park.</P>
                  <P>Coventry.</P>
                  <P>CV7 9JU.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Award of a one year plus one year contract to Mitie Technical Facilities Management to provide a total facilities management service for the University's High Temperature Research Centre (HTRC) facility on the Ansty Research Park in Coventry. This will include all the building maintenance services, security services, cleaning service, out of hours support services and support original equipment manufacturers for specialist machine maintenance.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>Mitie has provided TFM services to HTRC since it's opening in April 2015. Mitie has the knowledge and experience of current Rolls-Royce operations within investment loss wax process and TFM requirements within associated production facilities. Mitie also provides a specialist mobile support network of engineers at no additional fixed cost to the contract. They successfully mobilised the contract and have been providing advice and recommendations for improvements. It was envisaged that the University would tender the requirement or bring the services in-house. The in-house option is not feasible at present. It would also be difficult to provide adequate data for a tender specification due to data and operational variables. The HTRC is only now moving into a steady state operation after 28 months of running. This move into a steady state will provide an opportunity to collate accurate data and develop detailed specifications that reflect clear "steady state" requirements. The University would be in a position to go to market in 2020 with an informed specification.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
